Build a single-page React landing page for FixMe using Vite + Tailwind CSS v4.

## Theme

Dark background (#09090B), indigo brand accent (#6366F1 → #818CF8 gradient). Font: Inter via Google Fonts.

## Sections (top to bottom)

### Nav
- "FixMe" logo text (bold, white)
- Links: Features, How It Works, Languages
- "Download" CTA button (indigo gradient)

### Hero
- Large heading: "AI IT Support That Speaks Your Language"
- Subtitle about 5-language voice support and step-by-step fixes
- Two CTAs: "Download for Windows" (primary) and "View on GitHub" (outline)
- Animated gradient blur blobs (indigo/violet/purple) behind text
- Link to GitHub releases: `https://github.com/surindersingh1699/fixme/releases`

### Stats Row
- 3 stats: "5 Languages", "$0 Cost", "<30s Diagnosis"

### Features Grid
- 6 feature cards (2×3 grid on desktop, 1-col mobile):
  1. AI Screenshot Analysis — Claude Vision reads your screen
  2. Voice-Guided Fixes — Step-by-step with permission at each step
  3. 5-Language Support — EN, ES, PA, HI, FR with ElevenLabs TTS
  4. Screen Recording — Record sessions for documentation
  5. Smart Overlay — Transparent click-through annotations
  6. Zero Cost — Runs on free-tier APIs

### How It Works
- 3 numbered steps: Screenshot → AI Diagnosis → Guided Fix
- Each step with icon and description

### Languages
- Interactive 5-language selector (tabs)
- Each language shows a sample greeting and voice preview description

### Comparison Table
- "Without FixMe" vs "With FixMe" side-by-side
- 4 comparison points (time, language, cost, trust)

### CTA
- "Ready to Fix Smarter?" with download button

### Footer
- Built with Claude, ElevenLabs, PDD
- GitHub link, MIT license

## Technical

- Single App.jsx component with all sections
- Tailwind utility classes only (no custom CSS)
- Responsive: mobile-first with sm/md/lg breakpoints
- All external links open in new tab
- Smooth scroll for anchor links

## Dependencies

- React 19, Vite 7, Tailwind CSS v4 (@tailwindcss/vite plugin)
